Correct this Sudoku grid on the whiteboard into a valid complete solution, with the requirement of "minimum changes":
- Only modify the necessary digits, keeping changes to two cells or fewer;
- Do not alter the box dividing lines, do not change the doodle text "Rows aren't everything—check the columns too!", and do not modify the printed sheet content;
- After editing, every row, every column, and every 3×3 box must contain 1–9 exactly once each;
- The corrected digits must match the original dry-erase marker stroke style (line thickness, ink density variation, subtle ink breaks), appearing as natural as a localized stroke replacement in Photoshop;
- The glare/bright patch on the whiteboard must remain unchanged.
